<gco:CharacterString>GNIS contains point data derived from the federal Geographic Names Information System, depicting the locations of all named places in New Hampshire. Place name locations from the federal GNIS have been corrected and updated, based upon a variety of sources, including current and historic US Geological Survey topographic maps, aerial photography, New Hampshire state agency records, and current web sites.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>This data set will provide a quick reference for anyone wishing to determine what features in New Hampshire have names. It will also aid those wishing to name an unnamed feature in New Hampshire, by indicating whether duplicate or similar names exist elsewhere in the state.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:purpose> A feature class is a designation for a group of features in a broadly defined descriptive category. All features are assigned to one and only one class. They do not individually classify all kinds of cultural and natural features. By design, there are no Federal or industry standards or guidelines for feature classification.
